.orchestration/reports/U-F1-review-sonnet.md:3:Findings: (1) mod/high — update_gnss, update_msl_altitude, update_doppler_for_receiver, and Estimator::update() dispatcher (the exact path the executive calls) have ZERO test coverage. (2) minor/high — receiver-clock transition coupling (:377-379) never FD-verified. (3) minor/high — multi-nuisance retire-middle (≥2, non-last) untested; reindex logic verified manually only. (4) mod/med pnt-types:186-193 — covariance_accuracy uses sqrt(max(σx²,σy²)) not RSS/DRMS; under-reports up to √2 on the GPS_INPUT.horiz_accuracy safety path (aligns w/ Opus H1). (5) minor/med :448 — horizontal_velocity_ned_mps carries ECEF vx,vy (inherited from stub, unflagged; aligns w/ Opus M3). (6) info — single squashed commit, no red→green TDD evidence. (7) info — FilterState/SolutionEpoch lost Copy (harmless, verified). (8) info — git diff main noise is branch staleness, not scope violation.
.orchestration/reports/U-N1-review-sol.md:19:- LOW / high confidence / `docs/design/PARAMS_PROPOSAL.md:147-154,486-488` / Claim: 1.0 s is five times the nominal renewing-frame period. CONTRACTS v5.1 and the proposal itself say every accepted IMU propagation emits a DR-fill epoch, nominally about every 10 ms, so the implemented renewal opportunity is approximately 100 times faster than the lease, not five. Five times applies only to the baseline’s nominal 5 Hz navigation-output period. / How to verify: trace accepted IMU propagation through the executive into `IntegrityAuthorityGate::solution`, measure sequence-advance intervals, and describe separately the 100 Hz renewal cadence and 5 Hz publication cadence.
.orchestration/reports/U-N1-review-sol.md:23:The remaining checked arithmetic is correct: position `25/2 → 12` and `200/2 = 100`; heading conversions `1° = 0.017453 rad`, `2.5° = 0.043633 rad`; `6 h = 21,600 s`; 4 Hz maps to approximately 0.106 m/s at 11.3 GHz and 0.740 m/s at 1.62 GHz; `t_lease=1 s < 4 s < 5.071 s`. The aided-no-caution finding is real: aided G2 fails at 12 m before the 75 m caution test can be reached (`lib.rs:493-509,574-577`). All `AuthorityParams` fields are numerically represented, and the document repeatedly and unambiguously states PROPOSED/UNVERIFIED/no-authority status; nothing in it grants authority.
